Description:
Rare Steiff monkey 'Mungo' (1950s/1960s). Vintage mohair Steiff toy animal.
This gorgeous vintage Steiff monkey is utterly charming. He's looking for a very loving home.
As you will see from the photos, this gorgeous little monkey has clearly been well-loved. The many cuddles he must have received over the years have worn away some of his mohair fur in places, but these imperfections simply add to his charm.

- card chest tag is missing
- furry mane around his face are discoloured and worn in places
- mohair fur of body and tail is worn in a few places

Product name: Vintage Polished Steel Seiko Ship's Clock
Description:
We usually source vintage double-sided ships' clocks (as a sideline from our vintage maritime lighting), which are extremely popular. Now, for the smaller budget, we have tracked down these vintage gems.
These are original Seiko ships' clocks which would have been used on board vessels at sea, with all the heritage and backstory that goes with that - as well as looking incredible. Originally painted light blue-green (we have kept a few with this original paint - see our other listings - as it has a very distinct vintage feel), this version has been stripped of paint and the steel polished.
Originally run off the ship's electrical system, which is incompatible with domestic systems, we have had the electrics removed and the mechanism replaced with an extremely reliable battery version.
Clock dimensions: clock face diameter 18cm, back 22cm; depth 7cm.

Product name: Set of 2 Antique French Thread Double Spool Dispensers "Le Fil Au Chinois", Lithographed Tin Boxes, Polychrome, Collector item, France, 1920
Description:
Here is a Set of 2 Antique French Thread Double Spool Dispensers from the legendary French wire brand "Le fil au Chinois", famous in France and Europe until the beginning of the 20th century.
 This name of "Fil au Chinois" comes from a French era not so distant, in full mode of Orientalism. This popularity was provoked by the expeditions to Egypt in 1798 by Bonaparte, the conquest of Algeria by France (1830), the opening of China and Japan (1855). The birth of the Au Chinois brand is exactly part of this cultural movement and the idea was judicious because it allowed the creation of a person easily identifiable since it became an instant classic among collectors.
Whether to complete your collection or to revive them by using them again; They will surely maintain the passion in the heart all lovers of sewing!

Product name: Wooden Dog food stand, customizable dog food stand, elevated dog feeding stand, dog feeding stand, dog feeder, dog food, pet food, dog gift
Description:
Did you get a puppy for Christmas?  Do you have an older dog who needs some extra TLC?  Every dog owner needs a Buddy Bench aka a wooden dog food stand!   Makes the perfect dog gift!
This all began because of our own dog Buddy, an 8 year old Beagle. One day he was being a little too excited jumping up and down and actually ended up getting a sore neck.  The vet told us to have him take it easy and to elevate his food and water bowls.  We immediately went to the pet store to look for elevated dog feeding stands......they were expensive! And mostly made of plastic.  We realized that we could make our own customizable dog food stand out of wood that would not only be more beautiful, but also durable.  This led to building our very first Buddy Bench, a wooden dog feeding stand!
After more research we found out that ALL dogs would benefit from elevated dog food bowl stands.  It aids in digestion and helps prevent neck injuries.  We started building benches to accommodate all sizes of dogs, from the tiny to the large, from 6" tall to 18" tall.  We can even make them bigger if you have a super large breed.
Along with promoting good health we found that our benches solve another problem...dogs knocking their bowls over and pushing them around the house!  With our Buddy Bench, the beautiful stainless steel bowls are fitted inside the bench which prevents your dog from making a mess or knocking them around when empty.  Plus the bowls are super cute with their paw print design.  They come in 3 sizes, 24oz, 2qt, and 3qt depending on the size of your dog and their eating habits. 
It's not only dogs that can benefit from a Buddy Bench!  If you have a feline friend or other pet we can easily accommodate their needs as well.
Choose your height and choose your bowl size, and your pet food stand will be customized for your pet. 
Check out our other style of the Buddy Bench!

Product name: Precision Machined Spinning Top
Description:
The top, a time honored classic children's toy, with a precision machining twist. These built to order tops are precision machined using the latest in CNC manufacturing from your choice of materials. Each top is hand crafted in my shop, hand finished and hand tested/inspected before leaving for its new home. I am offering these in a multitude of different material types, each material has different looks and weights. 
Being precision machined, these tops have an incredible spin time, on average you can expect an aluminum top to spin for 1-2 minutes; although in testing in the shop I have seen them go for 5 minutes on the right surface. 
We are now also going to be offering a "Heat Anodized" finish to all materials with the exception of aluminum. This finish is created by heating the object with a torch to bring out an oxidation layer on the metal. The result is a colorful and unique finish, especially in Copper and Stainless Steel. When choosing this finish please keep in mind that the resulting finish and coloration will be unique to each top.
While tops are typically considered a children's' toy, we have found that these tops are wonderful for stress relief, entertainment and a great fidget tool for your desk! Whatever the purpose you can be assured that our precision solid metal tops will not disappoint. All prices include shipping and handling within the continental United States.

Product name: 5 Vintage Green Hardback Books, Youth Books, Paperback, Sci-Fi, Jules Verne Collection, Hachette, Bibliothèque Verte, France, 1970s
Description:
Here is a set of 5 classic vintage french hardback youth books. It is from Library series " Bibliothèque Verte" by Hachette (1976). The book has lots of beautiful colored illustrations made by the illustrator Jean Reschofsky and its hardback has appealing colors.  The first of them is "From the Earth to the Moon".
So give yourself a trip to the Moon, way before Wallace and Gromit does it with one of the Master of Science-Fiction, the French author Jules Vernes ! 
In this novel of adventures and anticipation, Jules Verne imagines an extraordinary and thrilling adventure: after the end of the Civil War, the Gun Club of Baltimore in the United States tries to send to the Moon a shell inhabited by three men.
The work has become a reference of science fiction, with many heirs such as the novel by HG Wells, The First Men in the Moon, in 1901. The novel has been adapted many times to the screen, For film and television, as early as 1902 with Georges Méliès and his "Voyage dans la Lune" (A trip to the Moon).
"From the Earth to the Moon" in its vintage youth book edition is the perfect give for nostalgia science-fiction fans and the nicest way for kids to learn French ! It has large easy-to-read type. As you can see on the pictures, the book would look lovely for an antique decoration or displayed on your personal library.
This Collection includes: 
" Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea " T.1 & T.2
" Five Weeks in a Balloon "
" The Carpathian Castle "

Product name: Papercraft Cats, Couple of Cats (2 PDF patterns), Paper Sculptures DIY, Low Polygon, Lowpoly Cats, DIY 3D Papercraft, First Anniversary Gift
Description:
Hello cat lover! This listing is a set of 2 digital templates you can download, print, cut, and put together using scissors (or craft knife) and white glue.
After several hours... Tadaaaaaaaaa! You get a cute pair of cats you will be so proud of!
These two files are bundled up to make you save 25% on the regular price.
Here is Gus, the standing cat: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/478105146
Here is Genevieve, the one climbing down the wall: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/477374714
************************************
Gus and Gevenieve are siblings that used to squabble all the time over their mother's attention. Now look at them, they are inseparable. Seems like squabbles make bonds stronger.
************************************
TECHNICALITIES
Total Height: 82cm/32in
Total Width: 10cm/4in
Total Depth: 38cm/15in
Total number of parts: 37  56 = 93 parts.
Bicolored models as usual, so each file is divided into 2 to make it easier for you to print: for each cat, one file for the body, and one file for eyes and ears.
************************************
LEVEL OF DIFFICULTY
3/5 (due to tiny parts)
The templates are pretty intuitive but if you have never made a paper sculpture before, each step of the illustrated instructions will suggest you where to start glueing the next part.
Plus the enclosed tips and tricks will help you make flawless sculptures easily.
************************************
ESTIMATED TIME
Allow one afternoon for the half cat to complete.
The standing cat may take up to a day, depending on your glue, number of breaks you need and how much of a perfectionist you are.
************************************
ABOUT GUS, THE STANDING CAT
Gus stands on his tail and back paws but needs to be pinned to the wall (there is a hole in his right front paw to do so). The enclosed instructions indicate where exactly to pin the pin on the wall.
He won't collapse if you use a 180-200 gsm paper (65-80 lbs) and above.
Caution: Much thicker paper will make the tiny parts much difficult to fold.
The common problem encountered when closing a paper sculpture has been solved with a simple solution my beta testers were grateful for :)
************************************
ABOUT GENEVIEVE, THE CAT CLIMBING DOWN
Hang it on the wall like a picture frame thanks to the triangular hole at the back.
160 gsm paper (65 lbs) is enough, but you can chose a heavier card stock.
 
************************************
This is an excellent exercice in patience, focus and mindfulness to free yourself from daily stress. But you already know that, right?
Download the templates of these cats and get in the zone!
